 12  * ECMA-262 5th edition Functions

 14 if (typeof Object.defineProperty !== 'function') {
 15     Object.defineProperty = function(obj, prop, desc) {
 16         if ('value' in desc) {
 17             obj[prop] = desc.value;
 18         }
 19         if ('get' in desc) {
 20             obj.__defineGetter__(prop, desc.get);
 21         }
 22         if ('set' in desc) {
 23             obj.__defineSetter__(prop, desc.set);
 24         }
 25         return obj;
 26     };
 27 }
 28 if (typeof Object.defineProperties !== 'function') {
 29     Object.defineProperties = function(obj, descs) {
 30         for (var prop in descs) {
 31             if (descs.hasOwnProperty(prop)) {
 32                 Object.defineProperty(obj, prop, descs[prop]);
 33             }
 34         }
 35         return obj;
 36     };
 37 }
 38 if (typeof Object.create !== 'function') {
 39     Object.create = function(prototype, descs) {
 40         function F() {
 41         }
 42 
 43         F.prototype = prototype;
 44         var obj = new F();
 45         if (descs != null) {
 46             Object.defineProperties(obj, descs);
 47         }
 48         return obj;
 49     };
 50 }
 51 if (typeof Object.getPrototypeOf !== 'function') {
 52     Object.getPrototypeOf = function(obj) {
 53         return obj.__proto__;
 54     };
 55 }

 57 if (typeof Function.prototype.bind !== 'function') {
 58     Function.prototype.bind = function(thisObject) {
 59         var func = this;
 60         var args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments, 1);
 61         var Nop = function() {
 62         };
 63         var bound = function() {
 64             var a = args.concat(Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments));
 65             return func.apply(
 66                 this instanceof Nop ? this : thisObject || window, a);
 67         };
 68         Nop.prototype = func.prototype;
 69         bound.prototype = new Nop();
 70         return bound;
 71     };
 72 }

 75 
 76     if (window.performance && window.performance.now) {
 77         return function() {
 78             return window.performance.now();
 79         };
 80     } else if (window.performance && window.performance.webkitNow) {
 81         return function() {
 82             return window.performance.webkitNow();
 83         };
 84     } else {
 85         return Date.now;
 86     }

 89 /**
 90  * define requestAnimationFrame
 91  */
 92 window.requestAnimationFrame =
 93     window.requestAnimationFrame ||
 94     window.mozRequestAnimationFrame ||
 95     window.webkitRequestAnimationFrame ||
 96     window.msRequestAnimationFrame ||
 97     (function() {
 98         var lastTime = window.getTime();
 99         var frame = 1000 / 60;
100         return function(func) {
101             var currentTime = window.getTime();
102             var _id = setTimeout(function() {
103                 func(window.getTime());
104             }, Math.max(0, lastTime + frame - currentTime));
105             lastTime = currentTime;
106             return _id;
107         };
108     }());

110 /**
111  * Export the library classes globally.
112  *
113  * When no arguments are given, all classes defined in enchant.js as well as all classes defined in
114  * plugins will be exported. When more than one argument is given, by default only classes defined
115  * in enchant.js will be exported. When you wish to export plugin classes you must explicitly deliver
116  * the plugin identifiers as arguments.
117  *
118  * @example
119  *   enchant();     // All classes will be exported.
120  *   enchant('');   // Only classes in enchant.js will be exported.
121  *   enchant('ui'); // enchant.js classes and ui.enchant.js classes will be exported.
122  *
123  * @param {...String} [modules] Export module. Multiple designations possible.
124  * @global
125  * @type {Object}
126  * @name enchant
127  */
128 var enchant = function(modules) {
129     if (modules != null) {
130         if (!(modules instanceof Array)) {
131             modules = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
132         }
133         modules = modules.filter(function(module) {
134             return [module].join();
135         });
136     }
137     (function include(module, prefix) {
138         var submodules = [],
139             i, len;
140         for (var prop in module) {
141             if (module.hasOwnProperty(prop)) {
142                 if (typeof module[prop] === 'function') {
143                     window[prop] = module[prop];
144                 } else if (typeof module[prop] === 'object' && Object.getPrototypeOf(module[prop]) === Object.prototype) {
145                     if (modules == null) {
146                         submodules.push(prop);
147                     } else {
148                         i = modules.indexOf(prefix + prop);
149                         if (i !== -1) {
150                             submodules.push(prop);
151                             modules.splice(i, 1);
152                         }
153                     }
154                 }
155             }
156         }
157 
158         for (i = 0, len = submodules.length; i < len; i++) {
159             include(module[submodules[i]], prefix + submodules[i] + '.');
160         }
161     }(enchant, ''));
162 
163     window.Game = window.Core;
164 
165     if (modules != null && modules.length) {
166         throw new Error('Cannot load module: ' + modules.join(', '));
167     }
168 };

175 window.addEventListener("message", function(msg, origin) {
176     try {
177         var data = JSON.parse(msg.data);
178         if (data.type === "event") {
179             enchant.Core.instance.dispatchEvent(new enchant.Event(data.value));
180         } else if (data.type === "debug") {
181             switch (data.value) {
182                 case "start":
183                     enchant.Core.instance.start();
184                     break;
185                 case "pause":
186                     enchant.Core.instance.pause();
187                     break;
188                 case "resume":
189                     enchant.Core.instance.resume();
190                     break;
191                 case "tick":
192                     enchant.Core.instance._tick();
193                     break;
194                 default:
195                     break;
196             }
197         }
198     } catch (e) {
199         // ignore
200     }
201 }, false);

203 /**
204  * @name enchant.Class
205  * @class
206  * A Class representing a class which supports inheritance.
207  *
208  * @param {Function} [superclass] The class from which the
209  * new class will inherit the class definition.
210  * @param {*} definition Class definition.
211  * @constructor
212  */
213 enchant.Class = function(superclass, definition) {
214     return enchant.Class.create(superclass, definition);
215 };
216 
217 /**
218  * Create a class.
219  *
220  * When defining classes that inherit from other classes, the previous class is used as a base with
221  * the superclass's constructor as default. When overriding the default constructor, it is necessary
222  * to explicitly call the previous constructor to ensure a correct class initialization.
223  *
224  * @example
225  *   var Ball = Class.create({ // Creates independent class.
226  *       initialize: function(radius) { ... }, // Method definition.
227  *       fall: function() { ... }
228  *   });
229  *
230  *   var Ball = Class.create(Sprite);  // Creates a class inheriting from "Sprite"
231  *   var Ball = Class.create(Sprite, { // Creates a class inheriting "Sprite"
232  *       initialize: function(radius) { // Overwrites constructor
233  *          Sprite.call(this, radius*2, radius*2); // Applies previous constructor.
234  *          this.image = core.assets['ball.gif'];
235  *       }
236  *   });
237  *
238  * @param {Function} [superclass] The class from which the
239  * new class will inherit the class definition.
240  * @param {*} [definition] Class definition.
241  * @static
242  */
243 enchant.Class.create = function(superclass, definition) {
244     if (superclass == null && definition){
245         throw new Error("superclass is undefined (enchant.Class.create)");
246     }else if(superclass == null){
247         throw new Error("definition is undefined (enchant.Class.create)");
248     }
249 
250     if (arguments.length === 0) {
251         return enchant.Class.create(Object, definition);
252     } else if (arguments.length === 1 && typeof arguments[0] !== 'function') {
253         return enchant.Class.create(Object, arguments[0]);
254     }
255 
256     for (var prop in definition) {
257         if (definition.hasOwnProperty(prop)) {
258             if (typeof definition[prop] === 'object' && definition[prop] !== null && Object.getPrototypeOf(definition[prop]) === Object.prototype) {
259                 if (!('enumerable' in definition[prop])) {
260                     definition[prop].enumerable = true;
261                 }
262             } else {
263                 definition[prop] = { value: definition[prop], enumerable: true, writable: true };
264             }
265         }
266     }
267     var Constructor = function() {
268         if (this instanceof Constructor) {
269             Constructor.prototype.initialize.apply(this, arguments);
270         } else {
271             return new Constructor();
272         }
273     };
274     Constructor.prototype = Object.create(superclass.prototype, definition);
275     Constructor.prototype.constructor = Constructor;
276     if (Constructor.prototype.initialize == null) {
277         Constructor.prototype.initialize = function() {
278             superclass.apply(this, arguments);
279         };
280     }
281 
282     var tree = this.getInheritanceTree(superclass);
283     for (var i = tree.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
284         if (typeof tree[i]._inherited === 'function') {
285             tree[i]._inherited(Constructor);
286             break;
287         }
288     }
289 
290     return Constructor;
291 };
292 
293 /**
294  * Get the inheritance tree of this class.
295  * @param {ConstructorFunction}
296  * @return {...ConstructorFunction}
297  */
298 enchant.Class.getInheritanceTree = function(Constructor) {
299     var ret = [];
300     var C = Constructor;
301     var proto = C.prototype;
302     while (C !== Object) {
303         ret.push(C);
304         proto = Object.getPrototypeOf(proto);
305         C = proto.constructor;
306     }
307     return ret;
308 };

419 /**
420  * @scope enchant.Event.prototype
421  */
422 enchant.Event = enchant.Class.create({
423     /**
424      * @name enchant.Event
425      * @class
426      * A class for an independent implementation of events
427      * similar to DOM Events.
428      * However, it does not include phase concept.
429      * @param {String} type Event type.
430      * @constructs
431      */
432     initialize: function(type) {
433         /**
434          * The type of the event.
435          * @type {String}
436          */
437         this.type = type;
438         /**
439          * The target of the event.
440          * @type {*}
441          */
442         this.target = null;
443         /**
444          * The x coordinate of the events occurrence.
445          * @type {Number}
446          */
447         this.x = 0;
448         /**
449          * The y coordinate of the events occurrence.
450          * @type {Number}
451          */
452         this.y = 0;
453         /**
454          * The event occurrences local coordinate systems x coordinates.
455          * @type {Number}
456          */
457         this.localX = 0;
458         /**
459          * The event occurrences local coordinate systems y coordinates.
460          * @type {Number}
461          */
462         this.localY = 0;
463     },
464     _initPosition: function(pageX, pageY) {
465         var core = enchant.Core.instance;
466         this.x = this.localX = (pageX - core._pageX) / core.scale;
467         this.y = this.localY = (pageY - core._pageY) / core.scale;
468     }
469 });

734 /**
735  * @scope enchant.EventTarget.prototype
736  */
737 enchant.EventTarget = enchant.Class.create({
738     /**
739      * @name enchant.EventTarget
740      * @class
741      * A class for an independent implementation of events
742      * similar to DOM Events.
743      * However, it does not include the phase concept.
744      * @extends {enchant.Event}
745      * @constructs
746      */
747     initialize: function() {
748         this._listeners = {};
749     },
750     /**
751      * Add a new event listener which will be executed when the event
752      * is being dispatched.
753      * @param {String} type Type of the events.
754      * @param {function(e:enchant.Event)} listener Event listener to be added.
755      */
756     addEventListener: function(type, listener) {
757         var listeners = this._listeners[type];
758         if (listeners == null) {
759             this._listeners[type] = [listener];
760         } else if (listeners.indexOf(listener) === -1) {
761             listeners.unshift(listener);
762 
763         }
764     },
765     /**
766      * Synonym for addEventListener
767      * @see {enchant.EventTarget#addEventListener}
768      * @param {String} type Type of the events.
769      * @param {function(e:enchant.Event)} listener Event listener to be added.
770      */
771     on: function() {
772         this.addEventListener.apply(this, arguments);
773     },
774     /**
775      * Delete an event listener.
776      * @param {String} type Type of the events.
777      * @param {function(e:enchant.Event)} listener Event listener to be deleted.
778      */
779     removeEventListener: function(type, listener) {
780         var listeners = this._listeners[type];
781         if (listeners != null) {
782             var i = listeners.indexOf(listener);
783             if (i !== -1) {
784                 listeners.splice(i, 1);
785             }
786         }
787     },
788     /**
789      * Clear all defined event listener for a given type.
790      * If no type is given, all listener will be removed.
791      * @param [String] type Type of the events.
792      */
793     clearEventListener: function(type) {
794         if (type != null) {
795             delete this._listeners[type];
796         } else {
797             this._listeners = {};
798         }
799     },
800     /**
801      * Issue an event.
802      * @param {enchant.Event} e Event to be issued.
803      */
804     dispatchEvent: function(e) {
805         e.target = this;
806         e.localX = e.x - this._offsetX;
807         e.localY = e.y - this._offsetY;
808         if (this['on' + e.type] != null){
809             this['on' + e.type](e);
810         }
811         var listeners = this._listeners[e.type];
812         if (listeners != null) {
813             listeners = listeners.slice();
814             for (var i = 0, len = listeners.length; i < len; i++) {
815                 listeners[i].call(this, e);
816             }
817         }
818     }

1192         /**

1194          *
1195          * Sets files which are to be preloaded. When {@link enchant.Core#start} is called the

1197          * is dispatched from the Core object. Depending on the type of the file different objects will be
1198          * created and stored in {@link enchant.Core#assets} Variable.
1199          * When an image file is loaded, an {@link enchant.Surface} is created. If a sound file is loaded, an
1200          * {@link enchant.Sound} object is created. Otherwise it will be accessible as a string.
1201          *
1202          * In addition, because this Surface object used made with {@link enchant.Surface.load},
1203          * direct object manipulation is not possible. Refer to the items of {@link enchant.Surface.load}
1204          *
1205          * @example
1206          *   core.preload('player.gif');
1207          *   core.onload = function() {
1208          *      var sprite = new Sprite(32, 32);
1209          *      sprite.image = core.assets['player.gif']; // Access via path
1210          *      ...
1211          *   };

1215          */

1222         /**
1223          * Loads a file.
1224          *
1225          * @param {String} asset File path of the resource to be loaded.
1226          * @param {Function} [callback] Function called up when file loading is finished.
1227          */

1229             if (callback == null) {
1230                 callback = function() {
1231                 };
1232             }
1233 
1234             var ext = enchant.Core.findExt(src);
1235 
1236             if (enchant.Core._loadFuncs[ext]) {
1237                 enchant.Core._loadFuncs[ext].call(this, src, callback, ext);
1238             }
1239             else {
1240                 var req = new XMLHttpRequest();
1241                 req.open('GET', src, true);
1242                 req.onreadystatechange = function(e) {
1243                     if (req.readyState === 4) {
1244                         if (req.status !== 200 && req.status !== 0) {
1245                             throw new Error(req.status + ': ' + 'Cannot load an asset: ' + src);
1246                         }
1247 
1248                         var type = req.getResponseHeader('Content-Type') || '';
1249                         if (type.match(/^image/)) {
1250                             core.assets[src] = enchant.Surface.load(src);
1251                             core.assets[src].addEventListener('load', callback);
1252                         } else if (type.match(/^audio/)) {
1253                             core.assets[src] = enchant.Sound.load(src, type);
1254                             core.assets[src].addEventListener('load', callback);
1255                         } else {
1256                             core.assets[src] = req.responseText;
1257                             callback();
1258                         }
1259                     }
1260                 };
1261                 req.send(null);
1262             }
1263         },
1264         /**
1265          * Start the core.
1266          *
1267          * Obeying the frame rate set in {@link enchant.Core#fps}, the frame in
1268          * {@link enchant.Core#currentScene} will be updated. If images to preload are present,
1269          * loading will begin and the loading screen will be displayed.

1308                     return asset in o ? false : o[asset] = true;
1309                 });

1311                     len = assets.length,

1331         /**

1346         /**
1347          * @private
1348          */

1355         },
1356         /**
1357          * @private
1358          */
1359         _checkTick: function(now) {
1360             var core = enchant.Core.instance;
1361             if (core._nextTime < now) {
1362                 // if enough time has passed, execute _tick
1363                 core._tick(now);
1364             } else {
1365                 // if enough time has not passed yet, request next frame
1366                 window.requestAnimationFrame(core._checkTick);
1367             }
1368         },
1369         _tick: function(now) {
1370             var e = new enchant.Event('enterframe');
1371             e.elapsed = now - this.currentTime;
1372 
1373             // frame fragment time, will be used in _checkTick
1374             this._nextTime = now + 1000 / this.fps;
1375             this._actualFps = e.elapsed > 0 ? (1000 / e.elapsed) : 0;
1376 
1377             var nodes = this.currentScene.childNodes.slice();
1378             var push = Array.prototype.push;
1379             while (nodes.length) {
1380                 var node = nodes.pop();
1381                 node.age++;
1382                 node.dispatchEvent(e);
1383                 if (node.childNodes) {
1384                     push.apply(nodes, node.childNodes);
1385                 }
1386             }
1387 
1388             this.currentScene.age++;
1389             this.currentScene.dispatchEvent(e);
1390             this.dispatchEvent(e);
1391 
1392             this.dispatchEvent(new enchant.Event('exitframe'));
1393             this.frame++;
1394             this._requestNextFrame();
1395         },
1396         getTime: function() {

1398         },
1399         /**
1400          * Stops the core.
1401          *
1402          * The frame will not be updated, and player input will not be accepted anymore.
1403          * Core can be restarted using {@link enchant.Core#start}.
1404          */
1405         stop: function() {
1406             this.ready = false;
1407             this.running = false;

1417         },

1431         /**
1432          * Switch to a new Scene.
1433          *
1434          * Scenes are controlled using a stack, and the display order also obeys that stack order.
1435          * When {@link enchant.Core#pushScene} is executed, the Scene can be brought to the top of stack.
1436          * Frames will be updated in the Scene which is on the top of the stack.
1437          *
1438          * @param {enchant.Scene} scene The new scene to be switched to.
1439          * @return {enchant.Scene} The new Scene.
1440          */
1441         pushScene: function(scene) {
1442             this._element.appendChild(scene._element);
1443             if (this.currentScene) {
1444                 this.currentScene.dispatchEvent(new enchant.Event('exit'));
1445             }
1446             this.currentScene = scene;
1447             this.currentScene.dispatchEvent(new enchant.Event('enter'));
1448             return this._scenes.push(scene);
1449         },
1450         /**
1451          * Ends the current Scene, return to the previous Scene.
1452          *
1453          * Scenes are controlled using a stack, and the display order also obeys that stack order.
1454          * When {@link enchant.Core#popScene} is executed, the Scene at the top of the stack
1455          * will be removed and returned.
1456          *
1457          * @return {enchant.Scene} Ended Scene.
1458          */
1459         popScene: function() {
1460             if (this.currentScene === this.rootScene) {
1461                 return this.currentScene;
1462             }
1463             this._element.removeChild(this.currentScene._element);
1464             this.currentScene.dispatchEvent(new enchant.Event('exit'));
1465             this.currentScene = this._scenes[this._scenes.length - 2];
1466             this.currentScene.dispatchEvent(new enchant.Event('enter'));
1467             return this._scenes.pop();
1468         },
1469         /**
1470          * Overwrites the current Scene with a new Scene.
1471          *
1472          * {@link enchant.Core#popScene}, {@link enchant.Core#pushScene} are executed after
1473          * each other to replace to current scene with the new scene.
1474          *
1475          * @param {enchant.Scene} scene The new scene which will replace the previous scene.
1476          * @return {enchant.Scene} The new Scene.
1477          */
1478         replaceScene: function(scene) {
1479             this.popScene();
1480             return this.pushScene(scene);

1484          *
1485          * Removes a Scene from the Scene stack.
1486          *
1487          * @param {enchant.Scene} scene Scene to be removed.
1488          * @return {enchant.Scene} The deleted Scene.
1489          */
1490         removeScene: function(scene) {
1491             if (this.currentScene === scene) {
1492                 return this.popScene();
1493             } else {
1494                 var i = this._scenes.indexOf(scene);
1495                 if (i !== -1) {

1497                     this._element.removeChild(scene._element);
1498                     return scene;
1499                 } else {

1501                 }
1502             }
1503         },

1534             this.addEventListener(button + 'buttonup', onxbuttonup);

1725     _updateCoordinate: function() {
1726         var node = this;
1727         var tree = [ node ];
1728         var parent = node.parentNode;
1729         var scene = this.scene;
1730         while (parent && node._dirty) {
1731             tree.unshift(parent);
1732             node = node.parentNode;
1733             parent = node.parentNode;
1734         }
1735         var matrix = enchant.Matrix.instance;
1736         var stack = matrix.stack;
1737         var mat = [];
1738         var newmat, ox, oy;
1739         stack.push(tree[0]._matrix);
1740         for (var i = 1, l = tree.length; i < l; i++) {
1741             node = tree[i];
1742             newmat = [];
1743             matrix.makeTransformMatrix(node, mat);
1744             matrix.multiply(stack[stack.length - 1], mat, newmat);
1745             node._matrix = newmat;
1746             stack.push(newmat);
1747             ox = (typeof node._originX === 'number') ? node._originX : node._width / 2 || 0;
1748             oy = (typeof node._originY === 'number') ? node._originY : node._height / 2 || 0;
1749             var vec = [ ox, oy ];
1750             matrix.multiplyVec(newmat, vec, vec);
1751             node._offsetX = vec[0] - ox;
1752             node._offsetY = vec[1] - oy;
1753             node._dirty = false;
1754         }
1755         matrix.reset();
1756     },

3077     makeTransformMatrix: function(node, dest) {
3078         var x = node._x;
3079         var y = node._y;
3080         var width = node.width || 0;
3081         var height = node.height || 0;
3082         var rotation = node._rotation || 0;
3083         var scaleX = (typeof node._scaleX === 'number') ? node._scaleX : 1;
3084         var scaleY = (typeof node._scaleY === 'number') ? node._scaleY : 1;
3085         var theta = rotation * Math.PI / 180;
3086         var tmpcos = Math.cos(theta);
3087         var tmpsin = Math.sin(theta);
3088         var w = (typeof node._originX === 'number') ? node._originX : width / 2;
3089         var h = (typeof node._originY === 'number') ? node._originY : height / 2;
3090         var a = scaleX * tmpcos;
3091         var b = scaleX * tmpsin;
3092         var c = scaleY * tmpsin;
3093         var d = scaleY * tmpcos;
3094         dest[0] = a;
3095         dest[1] = b;
3096         dest[2] = -c;
3097         dest[3] = d;
3098         dest[4] = (-a * w + c * h + x + w);
3099         dest[5] = (-b * w - d * h + y + h);

3103             a12 = m1[1], a22 = m1[3], ady = m1[5];
3104         var b11 = m2[0], b21 = m2[2], bdx = m2[4],
3105             b12 = m2[1], b22 = m2[3], bdy = m2[5];

3108         dest[1] = a12 * b11 + a22 * b12;
3109         dest[2] = a11 * b21 + a21 * b22;
3110         dest[3] = a12 * b21 + a22 * b22;
3111         dest[4] = a11 * bdx + a21 * bdy + adx;
3112         dest[5] = a12 * bdx + a22 * bdy + ady;
3113     },

3117             m12 = mat[1], m22 = mat[3], mdy = mat[5];

4624         return c * t / d + b;

4627      * @param t

4629      * @param c
4630      * @param d
4631      * @return {Number}
4632      */
4633     SWING: function(t, b, c, d) {
4634         return c * (0.5 - Math.cos(((t / d) * Math.PI)) / 2) + b;

4641      * @param d
4642      * @return {Number}

4644     QUAD_EASEIN: function(t, b, c, d) {
4645         return c * (t /= d) * t + b;

4666             return c / 2 * t * t + b;

4678     CUBIC_EASEIN: function(t, b, c, d) {
4679         return c * (t /= d) * t * t + b;

4682      * @param t
4683      * @param b
4684      * @param c
4685      * @param d
4686      * @return {Number}
4687      */
4688     CUBIC_EASEOUT: function(t, b, c, d) {

5567 enchant.Action = enchant.Class.create(enchant.ActionEventTarget, {
5568     /**
5569      * @name enchant.Action
5570      * @class
5571      * Action class.
5572      * Actions are units that make up the time line,
5573      * It is a unit used to specify the action you want to perform.
5574      * Action has been added to the time line is performed in order.
5575      *
5576      * Actionstart, actiontick event is fired when the action is started and stopped,
5577      * When one frame has elapsed actiontick event is also issued.
5578      * Specify the action you want to perform as a listener for these events.
5579      * The transition to the next action automatically the number of frames that are specified in the time has elapsed.
5580      *
5581      * @constructs
5582      * @param param
5583      * @config {integer} [time] The number of frames that will last action. infinite length is specified null
5584      * @config {function} [onactionstart] Event listener for when the action is initiated
5585      * @config {function} [onactiontick] Event listener for when the action has passed one frame
5586      * @config {function} [onactionend] Event listener for when the action is finished
5587      * @constructs
5588      */
5589     initialize: function(param) {
5590         enchant.ActionEventTarget.call(this);
5591         this.time = null;
5592         this.frame = 0;
5593         for (var key in param) {
5594             if (param.hasOwnProperty(key)) {
5595                 if (param[key] != null) {
5596                     this[key] = param[key];
5597                 }
5598             }
5599         }
5600         var action = this;
5601 
5602         this.timeline = null;
5603         this.node = null;
5604 
5605         this.addEventListener(enchant.Event.ADDED_TO_TIMELINE, function(evt) {
5606             action.timeline = evt.timeline;
5607             action.node = evt.timeline.node;
5608             action.frame = 0;
5609         });
5610 
5611         this.addEventListener(enchant.Event.REMOVED_FROM_TIMELINE, function() {
5612             action.timeline = null;
5613             action.node = null;
5614             action.frame = 0;
5615         });
5616 
5617         this.addEventListener(enchant.Event.ACTION_TICK, function(evt) {
5618             var remaining = action.time - (action.frame + evt.elapsed);
5619             if (action.time != null && remaining <= 0) {
5620                 action.frame = action.time;
5621                 evt.timeline.next(-remaining);
5622             } else {
5623                 action.frame += evt.elapsed;
5624             }
5625         });
5626 
5627     }
5628 });

5632 enchant.ParallelAction = enchant.Class.create(enchant.Action, {
5633     /**
5634      * @name enchant.ParallelAction
5635      * @class
5636      * @constructs
5637      * @extends enchant.Action
5638      */
5639     initialize: function(param) {
5640         enchant.Action.call(this, param);
5641         var timeline = this.timeline;
5642         var node = this.node;
5643         /**
5644          * Children Actions
5645          */
5646         this.actions = [];
5647         /**
5648          * Removed actions
5649          */
5650         this.endedActions = [];
5651         var that = this;
5652 
5653         this.addEventListener(enchant.Event.ACTION_START, function(evt) {
5654             for (var i = 0, len = that.actions.length; i < len; i++) {
5655                 that.actions[i].dispatchEvent(evt);
5656             }
5657         });
5658 
5659         this.addEventListener(enchant.Event.ACTION_TICK, function(evt) {
5660             var i, len, timeline = {
5661                 next: function(remaining) {
5662                     var action = that.actions[i];
5663                     that.actions.splice(i--, 1);
5664                     len = that.actions.length;
5665                     that.endedActions.push(action);
5666 
5667                     var e = new enchant.Event("actionend");
5668                     e.timeline = this;
5669                     action.dispatchEvent(e);
5670 
5671                     e = new enchant.Event("removedfromtimeline");
5672                     e.timeline = this;
5673                     action.dispatchEvent(e);
5674                 }
5675             };
5676 
5677             var e = new enchant.Event("actiontick");
5678             e.timeline = timeline;
5679             e.elapsed = evt.elapsed;
5680             for (i = 0, len = that.actions.length; i < len; i++) {
5681                 that.actions[i].dispatchEvent(e);
5682             }
5683 
5684             if (that.actions.length === 0) {
5685                 evt.timeline.next();
5686             }
5687         });
5688 
5689         this.addEventListener(enchant.Event.ADDED_TO_TIMELINE, function(evt) {
5690             for (var i = 0, len = that.actions.length; i < len; i++) {
5691                 that.actions[i].dispatchEvent(evt);
5692             }
5693         });
5694 
5695         this.addEventListener(enchant.Event.REMOVED_FROM_TIMELINE, function() {
5696             this.actions = this.endedActions;
5697             this.endedActions = [];
5698         });
5699 
5700     }

5705  */
5706 enchant.Tween = enchant.Class.create(enchant.Action, {
5707     /**
5708      * @name enchant.Tween
5709      * @class
5710      */
5711     initialize: function(params) {
5712         var origin = {};
5713         var target = {};
5714         enchant.Action.call(this, params);
5715 
5716         if (this.easing == null) {
5717             // linear
5718             this.easing = function(t, b, c, d) {
5719                 return c * t / d + b;
5720             };
5721         }
5722 
5723         var tween = this;
5724         this.addEventListener(enchant.Event.ACTION_START, function() {
5725             // excepted property
5726             var excepted = ["frame", "time", "callback", "onactiontick", "onactionstart", "onactionend"];
5727             for (var prop in params) {
5728                 if (params.hasOwnProperty(prop)) {
5729                     // if function is used instead of numerical value, evaluate it
5730                     var target_val;
5731                     if (typeof params[prop] === "function") {
5732                         target_val = params[prop].call(tween.node);
5733                     } else {
5734                         target_val = params[prop];
5735                     }
5736 
5737                     if (excepted.indexOf(prop) === -1) {
5738                         origin[prop] = tween.node[prop];
5739                         target[prop] = target_val;
5740                     }
5741                 }
5742             }
5743         });
5744 
5745         this.addEventListener(enchant.Event.ACTION_TICK, function(evt) {
5746             // if time is 0, set property to target value immediately
5747             var ratio = tween.time === 0 ? 1 : tween.easing(Math.min(tween.time,tween.frame + evt.elapsed), 0, 1, tween.time) - tween.easing(tween.frame, 0, 1, tween.time);
5748 
5749             for (var prop in target){
5750                 if (target.hasOwnProperty(prop)) {
5751                     if (typeof this[prop] === "undefined"){
5752                         continue;
5753                     }
5754                     tween.node[prop] += (target[prop] - origin[prop]) * ratio;
5755                     if (Math.abs(tween.node[prop]) < 10e-8){
5756                         tween.node[prop] = 0;
5757                     }
5758                 }
5759             }
5760         });
5761     }
5762 });

5765  */
